    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDate>2017-06-29</actionDate>
          <updateDate>2017-06-29T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill amends the Secure Rural Schools and Community Self-Determination Act of 2000 to modify the authorized uses of funds a county elects to receive under such Act to include:</p> <ul> <li> reimbursing the county for law enforcement patrols and evacuations that are performed on federal land;</li> <li>search and rescue preparedness training; and </li> <li>capital equipment, equipment maintenance, and other purchases related to carrying out search and rescue and other emergency services. </li> </ul> <p>A participating county may reallocate funds for a different use than authorized only after the 45-day public comment period has ended, at the beginning of which the county shall publish a description of how it proposes to use the funds. </p> <p>The bill extends the authority for the initiation of county projects until the end of FY2019 and allows county funds to remain available until expended. </p>]]></text>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-04-19T14:12:05Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
